Mafdet's route surveyors have confirmed that lava serpents are the primary transit hazard on the Ember Crown's Firsttooth approach lanes. Three serpent kills will establish baseline territorial data and give the harbor authority enough behavioral information to determine whether the approach can be kept clear with periodic culling operations or requires structural rerouting of the entire mineral transit path.
Three lava serpent kills are logged and Mafdet's route analysts are satisfied that territorial behavior confirms culling rather than rerouting as the viable management approach. The harbor authority is updating the Firsttooth approach authorization to include a mandatory quarterly cull contract as a condition of all bonded mineral transit licenses through the Ember Crown range.
